commit.message:
Thank all the pyldap contributors

The patches wil be squashed for python-ldap.
Put all authors and a link to the full history in the credits section.
Re-brand back to python-ldap
Tests: Import t_bind from __init__
message.c: Create pydn just before it's needed

syncrepl.py: Remove comments with stale links

python-ldap has the same code, but without the comments

Remove unneeded aliases in the C API

Python 2.7 has these built-in

Import StringIO from io

The io module was backported to Python 2.7. It uses the C-optimized
version, so cStringIO is not needed either.

Remove reference to "upstream" in a comment

(The new wording parallels other comments in the file)
Remove ldap.PYLDAP_VERSION, as we're not pyldap any more
README: Deprecate pyldap; move bytes discussion to documentation

Revert bad/unnecessary differences from python-ldap

One of these is a SyntaxError caused by mis-merge,
others are whitespace or naming fixes

Demo/ldapurl_search: use print_function future import

Unicode literals are not needed here.
Fix typo in .gitignore
Merge changes cherry-picked from python-ldap's development branch

Merge Michael's work from the CVS repository on SourceForge

This includes changes from the 2.5.2 and (unfinished) 2.5.3 branches,
excluding those that do extensive code reformatting. The list
of those follows.
